WASM ptr/len read-guard invariant: EVERY new Uint8Array(memory.buffer, ptr, len) on a wasm-RETURNED (ptr|len<<32) result must pass through guardWasmRange first, else a large/overflowed ptr/len throws V8's raw 'Start offset outside the bounds of the buffer' and crashes the watcher dispatch loop. The watcher dispatch decode and the CLI dispatch decode in plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js were unguarded (only the main dispatch_verb path was); guarded -> the watcher try/catch returns {ok:false,error:'wasm-memory-read-out-of-bounds'} instead of bricking, so a state-read on oversized state degrades gracefully and survives reboots. Input-WRITE .set() paths (alloc'd ptr + agent-bounded length) are safe and need no guard. BROWSER SCREENSHOT recipe: page.screenshot() returns a PNG Buffer; returning it inline stringifies to useless bytes -- instead page.screenshot({path}) then Read that path (the Read tool renders the PNG). Same for any binary: write to a path, Read the path.